Use **`WebApplicationFactory<TEntryPoint>`** from `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing`. It spins up your app in-process with an in-memory test server — no real ports, no real HTTP listener.

### Setup

```bash
dotnet add tests/MyMcp.Tests package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing
```

### Example test

```csharp
public class McpIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public McpIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _client = factory.CreateClient();
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Initialize_ReturnsCapabilities()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 1,
            method = "initialize",
            @params = new
            {
                protocolVersion = "2025-03-26",
                clientInfo = new { name = "test-client", version = "1.0" },
                capabilities = new { }
            }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        Assert.Equal("2025-03-26",
            body.GetProperty("result")
                .GetProperty("protocolVersion")
                .GetString());
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task ToolsList_ReturnsRegisteredTools()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 2,
            method = "tools/list",
            @params = new { }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        var tools = body.GetProperty("result").GetProperty("tools");
        Assert.True(tools.GetArrayLength() > 0);
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **No real server** — `WebApplicationFactory` hosts your app in-memory and routes requests through the pipeline directly.
- **Full pipeline** — middleware, routing, DI, auth — everything runs exactly as in production.
- **Override services** — use `factory.WithWebApplicationFactory(b => b.ConfigureServices(...))` to swap in mocks (e.g., stub a database).
- Make sure `Program` is accessible to the test project (add `InternalsVisibleTo` or a `public partial class Program { }` marker).

If your MCP server uses **SSE (Streamable HTTP)**, you can read the streaming response with `HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead` and parse the SSE event stream line-by-line from the response content stream.
